  "prompt": "Is it true that diet soda kills brain cells because they use so many chemicals to make it \"diet\"?",
  "response": "No, this is a myth. There is no scientific evidence that diet soda kills brain cells. While diet sodas do contain artificial sweeteners and other chemicals, current research has not shown that these ingredients directly cause brain cell death. \n\nSome studies have suggested potential health concerns related to artificial sweeteners, such as:\n- Potential links to metabolic changes\n- Possible effects on gut bacteria\n- Some associations with increased risk of certain health conditions\n\nHowever, these studies are not conclusive, and moderate consumption of diet soda has not been proven to cause direct harm to brain cells. As with many foods and drinks, moderation is key. If you have specific health concerns, it's best to consult with a healthcare professional.",
